<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="526" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-14"><hi rend="italic">June 14,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 941.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 868 of the 3d instant, with
                            inclosures, has been received.</p>
                        <p>The Department has noted with appreciation the readiness with which His
                            Majesty’s Government acceded to the request to authorize Mr. Elliot to
                            take temporary charge of American interests in Bulgaria.</p>
                        <p>You will express to Lora Lansdowne this Government’s thanks for the
                            courtesy so promptly extended.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>